1. What is Backend?
The back end refers to parts of a computer application or a 
program's code that allow it to operate and that cannot be 
accessed by a user. Most data and operating syntax are stored 
and accessed in the back end of a computer system.

2. What are the advantages of using Node JS?
High Performance.
Scalability.
Easy to Learn.
Reduces Loading time using caching.
Improves Response time and boosts performance.
Large Community Support.
Cost-Effective.
Extensibility.